13:20 5000m in Xiamen and man was I absolutely cooked after this one. 80 degrees ( 93% humidity ) was just something the body was not ready for and I paid the iron price for it. Was basically blackout drunk post race. Throwing up / unresponsive / couldn’t weight bare so ended up taking a nice tour of the local hospital here in Xiamen after symptoms didn’t progress. Just couldn’t cooldown / self regulate. All good now and was cleared to come back to hotel later that night. Proud of myself for digging deep and being able to put together a decent race all things considered. Felt pretty good in the race and executed well I thought but obviously went to far past the “line” in this one. Staggered my way the last 200m. Hoping to be able to bounce back after a few rest days. 🤞🏼🤞🏼
